  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6906 sitting just above the massive +10.3B gamma wall at 6900, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any further upside momentum to hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime with 97B total GEX creates a strong gravitational pull toward the 6900 strike, where maximum positive gamma concentration will trigger heavy dealer selling on rallies. Key levels to monitor: 6900 (max selling pressure), 6852 GEX flip (regime change threshold), and the 7000 wall (+8.9B) as the next major resistance if momentum breaks through current levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6900 with limited upside potential due to heavy dealer selling pressure.",
